rules.sql: allergyId IS NOT NULL AND allergyId != ''
rules.name: AllergyIDmustbepresent

rules.sql: patientMrn IS NOT NULL AND patientMrn != ''
rules.name: PatientMRNmustbepresent

rules.sql: allergenCode IS NOT NULL AND allergenCode != ''
rules.name: Allergencodemustbepresent

rules.sql: allergenCodeSystem IS NOT NULL AND allergenCodeSystem != ''
rules.name: Allergencodesystemmustbepresent
rules.description: Allergen code system must be present

rules.sql: allergenName IS NOT NULL AND allergenName != ''
rules.name: Allergennamemustbepresent
AllergencodesshoulduseRxNorm,SNOMEDCT,orUNII
rules.description: Allergen codes should use RxNorm, SNOMED-CT, or UNII

rules.sql: allergyType IS NULL OR allergyType = '' OR allergyType IN ('Drug allergy', 'Food allergy', 'Environmental allergy', 'Intolerance')
rules.name: Allergytypeshouldusestandardcategories
rules.description: Allergy type should use standard categories

rules.sql: severity IS NULL OR severity = '' OR severity IN ('255604002', '6736007', '24484000', '399166001')
rules.name: SeverityshouldusestandardSNOMEDCTcodes
rules.description: Severity should use standard SNOMED-CT codes

rules.sql: reaction IS NOT NULL AND reaction != ''
rules.name: reactionsshouldbedocumented

rules.sql: onsetDate IS NULL OR onsetDate = '' OR onsetDate <= CURRENT_DATE
rules.name: Allergydatesshouldbereasonable

rules.sql: recordedDate IS NULL OR recordedDate = '' OR recordedDate <= CURRENT_DATE
rules.name: recordedDatedatesshouldbereasonable

rules.sql: status IS NULL OR status = '' OR status IN ('active', 'inactive', 'resolved')
rules.name: Allergystatusshouldindicatecurrentstate
rules.description: Allergy status should indicate current state
